    <div class="LessonContent__main">

      <!-- summary -->
      <div class="LessonContent__section">

        <div class="LessonContent__heading">Summary</div>

        <div class="LessonContent__quick_pitch">
          This project, focuses on creating geographical tiles using primitive shapes in Tinkercad.
        </div>

        <div class="LessonContent__summary">
          In this project, your students will learn how to use a free program called Tinkercad. Using Tinkercad students will design basic geographical tiles to represent various environments. When the tiles are combined, students can create a country and learn about geography and colonialism.
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- objectives -->
      <div class="LessonContent__section">

        <div class="LessonContent__heading">Objectives</div>

        <div class="LessonContent__objective">
          Explore the history of colonialism, research the geography of different regions
        </div>

        <div class="LessonContent__objective">
          Understand the importance of natural resources, learn basic principles of economics (supply and demand)
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- outcomes -->
      <div class="LessonContent__section">

        <div class="LessonContent__heading">Expected outcomes</div>

        <div class="LessonContent__thumbnails">

          <% 3.times do |i| %>
